Common tools used by the kernel team
------------------------------------

buildscripts: Scripts used to farm out the kernel builds to very fast remote
machines that are part of the kernel team build infrastructure

chroot-setup: Scripts to setup jailed kernel compilation enviroments.

daily-test-isos: Scripts and support files to produce daily, custom test isos.

git-hooks: Optional hooks to save you from making dumb mistakes when
committing patches

maintscripts: Scripts used for general / stable kernel maintenance

mainline-build: Scripts to produce .debs for mainline kernels

misc: Everything else...


Documentation
------------------------------------

General: https://canonical-kteam-docs.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/index.html

Stable Patch Format: https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Kernel/Dev/StablePatchFormat

